09/10/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- A delegation led by US Ambassador to NATO Nicholas Burns met with Prime Minister Fatos Nano in Tirana on Tuesday (8 October) to review the progress of military reforms. 
Burns welcomed recent structural reforms in the country and the measures taken against corruption and organised crime, but suggested more could be done. 
Nano confirmed Albania's firm commitment to streamline reforms to meet the country's strategic goals for EU and NATO integration. 
He also expressed the desire to intensify relations with NATO and described the United States as a strategic partner. 
(ATA - 08/10/02)
